Question: Three congruent isosceles triangles $DAO$, $AOB$ and $OBC$ have $AD=AO=OB=BC=10$ and $AB=DO=OC=12$.  These triangles are arranged to form trapezoid $ABCD$, as shown.  Point $P$ is on side $AB$ so that $OP$ is perpendicular to $AB$.

[asy]
pair A, B, C, D, O, P;
A= (6, 8);
B=(18, 8);
C=(24, 0);
D=(0,0);
O=(12,0);
P=(12,8);
draw(A--B--C--D--A);
draw(A--O--B);
draw(O--P, dashed);
label("A", A, NW);
label("B", B, NE);
label("C", C, SE);
label("D", D, SW);
label("O", O, S);
label("P", P, N);
label("12", (D+O)/2, S);
label("12", (O+C)/2, S);
label("10", (A+D)/2, NW);
label("10", (B+C)/2, NE);
[/asy]

